description_english:
Responsibilities:
1. Responsible for sales work within the designated region, focusing on sales for an integrated logistics and trade platform;
2. Implement consultative selling and maintain existing client resources;
3. Regularly visit clients to establish, develop, and maintain key client relationships;
4. Ensure the collection of sales payments, and accept and assist in handling customer complaints;
5. Cooperate with the marketing and sales departments to carry out relevant market activities in the assigned sales area, and collect and provide timely feedback on market information to the company;
6. Develop work plans, conduct regular work summaries, and complete relevant sales reports.
Requirements:
1. College degree or above;
2. 10+ years of work experience, with 5+ years of experience in dealing with state-owned enterprise (SOE) platform companies;
3. Possess a deep network of government resources (Transportation, Industry and Information Technology), with excellent communication and negotiation skills with high-level government officials, and experience in digital project operations;
4. Responsible for solution selling in the assigned region; possess a strong sense of ambition, able to handle nationwide business travel and high-intensity work, with good professional ethics and problem-solving abilities.

Job Responsibilities:
1. Participate in the development and maintenance of blockchain frontend projects;
2. Participate in the development of related peripheral applications and DApps, build ecological content, and improve system security and stability;
3. Collaborate with the team to design and implement innovative blockchain solutions to enhance user experience;
4. Responsible for establishing frontend code specifications, monitoring code quality, etc.;
5. Write high-quality code, and conduct thorough testing and debugging.
Job Requirements:
1. Proficient in mainstream web frontend technologies such as JS, Vue 2, Vue 3, proficient in ES5 and ES6 syntax, with over 3 years of practical business frontend development experience using these technologies.
2. Able to quickly analyze and develop based on user requirements and UI design, have solutions for mainstream browser and mobile compatibility issues, and possess rich experience in UI and responsive development.
3. Proficient in component-oriented frontend development patterns, with relevant experience in component planning and encapsulation.
4. Familiar with backend interaction methods and server configuration and deployment.
5. Strong learning ability (especially important), passionate about new fields and technologies, willing to research (please do not apply if you are not interested).
6. Experience with Web3 and MetaMask integration is a plus.
